Which of the following commands locks out password- based login for a user but does notprevent other forms of login?
A)  usermod - L
B)  userdel - r
C)  useradd - h
D)  userlock
A
A. The usermod - L command locks an account by placing an ! in the encrypted password.If the user has another means to log in, such as with an SSH key, using usermod - L will notprevent their login. Among the other answers, userdel - r deletes a user and useradd - hdisplays help related to adding a user to the system. There is no userlock command.
